{{DISPLAYTITLE:Level 526: All Theatres Are Haunted}}
{{Class Ψ}}
Level 526 is the 527<sup>th</sup> level of the Backrooms.
==Description==
{{Blurimage|file=T11 Tennessee-Theater-1920s.jpg|caption=One of the few clear pictures taken of the level. Fig_2.0}}
Level 526, commonly referred to as "All Theatres Are Haunted," is an interlinked network of historic theatres, each resembling 19th and early 20th-century venues. Structures within the level consist of ornate architecture, including velvet curtains, gold leaf molding, and tiered balconies. The level seems to have a property that cleans itself when dirty. The lights in the level illuminate a dim area, and an unusually anxious sensation is felt when near one. This level is responsible for constant auditory and visual hallucinations, despite none of it being real. Oddly, these hallucinations cannot be cured by any variant of [[Object 1|Almond Water]], but can be ignored.

{{Blurimage|file=CorruptedPicture.png|caption=A picture taken of the level under the level's properties. Fig_1.0}}The level is most infamous for its paranormal qualities. The level manifests hallucinations that can actively change the environment within the level, only if the wanderer '''truly''' believes that the hallucinations are real. If one can acknowledge the fact that these hallucinations are not real, they will not affect the present structure or environment of the level. However, these hallucinations are hard to avoid. his level suffers from [[Phenomenon 15]]. Whispers, screams, and distorted speech can be heard echoing from within auditoriums or empty halls, and the conversations are often specific, describing murders or repeating rumors of "hauntings" within the theatre. Paintings and portraits are present, mounted on the walls. If one is suffering from visual hallucinations, the eyes on a painting with a face will move and watch the wanderer. These face paintings usually depict stiff, pallid faces or grotesque expressions. Mirrors often display a distorted reflection of the observer’s face, and some claim they show unfamiliar figures standing just behind them. At times, faint orchestral or organ music drifts through the air, soft but uncomfortably calming.

Electronic devices are occasionally rendered nonfunctional. Phones, laptops, flashlights, and even digital watches may fail as if being tampered with by a supernatural force. Cameras almost always produce corrupted or incomprehensible images when used, but in rare instances, they capture recognizable photographs. These successful pictures consistently display a monochrome, grainy texture reminiscent of photographs taken with early cameras from the late 1800s.

The climate within the level is extremely cold, with temperatures frequently falling below 0°C, usually stabilizing at -15°C. The coldest areas are often the most dangerous, coinciding with heightened paranormal activity and more extreme EMF fluctuations. It is very rare, but certain areas of the level can be room temperature or even warm; these areas are notable for their complete lack of paranormal disturbances, making them the safest places within Level 526.

Level 526 follows Non-Euclidean geometry, wanderers often walk in circles despite taking straight or diverging paths, and theatres loop back into themselves in inconsistent ways. Furniture and stage props are sometimes arranged in irregular and obstructive positions; attempting to move them will fail, however it is unknown why. Windows are rare to come across; however, if one were to find a window, they reveal pitch-black voids, bearing similarities to [[The Void]]. A faint ambiance of low buzzing, along with occasional crowd chatter or the muffled sound of footsteps from above, can also be heard, further enhancing the impression that the level is never truly empty.

==Entities==
Over the past 15 years of the level's discovery, no common entities have been spotted in the level. Though many strange sightings have been reported very frequently, presumed to be hallucinations, though some may not. Currently, the only sighted and documented entities in this level are [[Entity 10|Skin-Stealers]].

==Colonies and Outposts==
Due to the mental hazards present within the level, colonies and outposts are unfeasible.
==Entrances and Exits==
===Entrances===
*Staying in [[Level 444]] for a long time can bring one here.
*One may enter this level by No-Clipping through a TV on [[level 5]].
*Entering a cinema on [[Level 11]] may bring one to the theatre seats of this level.
===Exits===
*Going through exit doors will bring one to a random level.
*Entering the backstage of the theatre will bring one back to [[Level 444]].
*Breaking a window will send one to [[The Void]].

